  The current Thread.sleep(100) model is incompatible with deterministic video export. The fix is deltaTime, and it's architectural — it has to be built in from the start, not added
  later.                                                                                                                                                                              
                                                            
  The key insight is that preview mode and export mode are the same render loop with different time sources:                                                                          
                                                            
  protocol FrameLoop {                                                                                                                                                                
      func tick(update: (Double) -> Void, draw: (CGContext) -> Void)
  }                                                                                                                                                                                   
   
  // Preview: CADisplayLink drives real-time, deltaTime = actual elapsed time                                                                                                         
  class DisplayLinkFrameLoop: FrameLoop { ... }             
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  // Export: no display, deltaTime = 1.0 / targetFPS, runs as fast as CPU allows                                                                                                      
  class ExportFrameLoop: FrameLoop { ... }                                                                                                                                            
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  Every update(deltaTime:) call advances animation state by exactly that duration. Export mode feeds 1.0/fps deterministically — the same project always produces identical output    
  regardless of machine speed. This also means a 60-second animation at 30fps is exactly 1800 render calls, which you can progress-bar and time.
                                                                                                                                                                                      
