  CoreGraphics, AVFoundation, and CADisplayLink are identical APIs on both platforms. The engine package genuinely does not need to know which platform it's running on.              
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  The one real difference: input                                                                                                                                                      
                                                            
  The current keyboard/mouse/9-DOF-camera model doesn't translate to touch. But this is actually an opportunity rather than a problem — the camera control in the Scala engine was    
  always a rough tool. On iOS the natural model is:         
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  - Pinch → zoom/scale                                                                                                                                                                
  - Two-finger drag → pan camera
  - Two-finger rotate → rotate                                                                                                                                                        
  - Tap → select / trigger                                  
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  On macOS these same gestures work on a trackpad, with keyboard shortcuts as an additional layer. SwiftUI handles gesture recognition uniformly across both platforms. The           
  InteractionManager equivalent becomes a CameraController that accepts normalised gestures rather than raw VK key codes — cleaner on both platforms.
                                                                                                                                                                                      
  The one version constraint                                

  CADisplayLink on macOS requires macOS 14 (Sonoma). Before Sonoma, macOS used CVDisplayLink (a different, C-level API). If you need macOS 13 compatibility you'd need a small shim.  
  Given you're starting new development now, targeting macOS 14+ is reasonable and gives you API parity with iOS 17+.
                                                                                                                                                                                      
