    Delta-time: What's actually involved                                                    
                                                                                                                                                                
  The plumbing already exists. Engine.update(deltaTime:) already receives real wall-clock delta from CADisplayLink — it just throws it away and calls           
  loomEngine.advance(). The top-level wiring is done; only the interior needs work.                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                
  The job breaks into four layers of increasing difficulty:                                                                                                     
  
  ---                                                                                                                                                           
  Layer 1 — Signature propagation (30 min, trivial)         
                                                                                                                                                                
  Pass deltaTime down the call chain:
  - LoomEngine.advance() → advance(deltaTime: Double)                                                                                                           
  - SpriteScene.advance(using:) → advance(deltaTime: Double, using:)
  - Engine.update already calls both — just update the calls                                                                                                    
                                                            
  ---                                                                                                                                                           
  Layer 2 — Keyframe time-basing (2–3 hours, moderate)
                                                                                                                                                                
  The hard part. Keyframe drawCycle values in XML are integer frame numbers (e.g., 0, 30, 60, 90). To go time-based you must decide: what frame rate did the 
  Scala engine assume?                                                                                                                                          
                                                            
  Options:                                                                                                                                                      
  - Add targetFPS to GlobalConfig (default 30) — multiply deltaTime * targetFPS to get a fractional cycle count, then pass Double time to TransformAnimator
  instead of Int cycle. Fully XML-compatible.                                                                                                                   
  - Reinterpret XML values as milliseconds — breaking change, requires migrating all project files.
                                                                                                                                                                
  The first option is the right call. TransformAnimator would accumulate elapsedTime in SpriteInstance.state, and normalizedCycle becomes                       
  normalizedTime(elapsed: Double, totalSeconds: Double, loopMode:).                                                                                             
                                                                                                                                                                
  ---                                                                                                                                                           
  Layer 3 — RenderStateEngine palette stepping (2–4 hours, significant)
                                                                       
  Currently steps one palette entry per frame — no duration concept. For true delta-time it needs fractional accumulation: PaletteIndexState gains a
  timeAccumulator: Double, and RendererChanges gets a "seconds per step" field (or steps per second). This is a config format change.                           
  
  This is the fiddly layer. The Scala engine also stepped one per frame, so current Swift behaviour already matches Scala. The only real problem is if the app  
  runs at a different frame rate than Scala's default.      
                                                                                                                                                                
  ---                                                       
  Layer 4 — Meander noise phase (1–2 hours, moderate)
                                                     
  PathPerturbation.perturb(edge:config:edgeIndex:frame:...) uses frame: Int for noise phase offset. Replace with elapsedTime: Double and use elapsedTime * 
  frequency instead of frame * frequency.                                                                                                                       
  
  ---                                                                                                                                                           
  Summary                                                   

  ┌──────────────────────────┬────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │          Layer           │  Time  │                               Risk                               │
  ├──────────────────────────┼────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 1. Signature propagation │ 30 min │ None                                                             │
  ├──────────────────────────┼────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ 2. Keyframe time-basing  │ 2–3 hr │ Low — XML-compatible if targetFPS added to GlobalConfig          │                                                      
  ├──────────────────────────┼────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤                                                      
  │ 3. Palette stepping      │ 2–4 hr │ Medium — config format change needed for proper duration control │                                                      
  ├──────────────────────────┼────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤                                                      
  │ 4. Meander phase         │ 1–2 hr │ Low                                                              │
  └──────────────────────────┴────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘                                                      
                                                            
  Minimum useful increment: Layers 1 + 2 give you frame-rate-independent keyframe animation in ~3 hours with zero XML migration. Layers 3 and 4 can wait — the  
  current frame-counting behaviour matches Scala exactly for palette and meander.
                                                                                                                                                                
  The main gotcha: every project's drawCycle values were authored against Scala's actual frame rate. If you don't know what that was, you'll need to calibrate  
  targetFPS by feel against the Scala output. For most Loom projects, 30 fps is the safe assumption.

